            "is_prior_year_field": false,
            "draft_value": "* Directly supports high-tech activity in UT-02, which received over $780,000 in NASA Science obligations between FY 2023 and FY 2025.\n* Sustains critical grants for district institutions including Innosys, Inc. ($728,997) and the Utah Geological Survey ($247,550).\n* Provides economic opportunities for local small businesses such as Star Cases LLC, which has received NASA contracts to support mission requirements.\n* Bolsters Utah's broader aerospace economy and STEM pipeline by funding the complex technical challenges that drive local innovation and workforce training.",
